HEADWORD: Head-cheese
<hw>Head"-cheese`</hw> <pr>(h⟦ecr⟧d"ch⟦emac⟧z`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A dish made of portions of the head, or head and feet, of swine,
cut up fine, seasoned, and pressed into a cheeselike mass.</def>⟦br⟧
